condition.narrative: Finance Agreement: Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section II, Paragraph B.4 | Description: The Recipient shall recruit aninternal auditor to the PCU staff and adopt acceptable revised TOR for the recruitment of the auditors referred to in Section4.09(b) of the General Conditions | Due Date :11-Apr-2012

Finance Agreement: Financing Agreement, Paragraph 4.02 | Description: The co-financing deadline for the effectiveness of theco-financing agreement for NGO financing is September 30, 2013 | Due Date :30-Sep-2013

Finance Agreement: Financing Agreement, Schedule 2, Section IV, Paragraph B.1 (b) | Description: No withdrawals from the IDA creditshall be made in relation to any NGO, unless the Delegated Management Contract or Service Contract is acceptable to the Bank. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement: Financing Agreement: Paragraph 4.01(c) | Description: The Recipient shall apply sound social, environmental andecological standards and practices to PAs, to avoid compromising the achievement of project objectives and raising reputationalrisks | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement: Financing Agreement: Paragraph 4.01(d) | Description: The Recipient shall not repeal, waive, suspend, set aside,or fail to enforce Decree 2010-141 prohibiting the cutting, extraction or export of rosewood and ebony, or any provisions thereof |Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement: Financing Agreement: Paragraph 4.01(e) | Description: The Recipient shall execute an administrative order orother instrument purporting to delegate authority to NGOs | Due Date :31-Dec-2011
Finance Agreement: Financing Agreement: Paragraph 5.01(a) | Description: The Recipient shall execute subsidiary agreements withMadagascar National Parks and the Foundation. | Due Date :11-Jan-2012

Finance Agreement: Financing Agreement: Paragraph 5.01(b) | Description: The Recipient shall execute the GEF Grant Agreement andfulfill all conditions precedent to its effectiveness or to the right to make withdrawals. | Due Date :11-Jan-2012

Finance Agreement: Financing Agreement: Paragraph 5.01(c) | Description: The Recipient shall establish a Project SteeringCommittee, Project Coordination Unit and prepare and adopt a Project Implementation Plan. | Due Date :11-Jan-2012

Finance Agreement: Financing Agreement: Schedule II, Section 1, F, Paragraph 1 | Description: The Recipient shall ensure that theproject activities are implemented in accordance with the safeguards instruments applicable to the additional financing. |Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement: GEF Grant Agreement: Paragraph 5.01(d) | Description: The Foundation shall update its Administrative andFinancial Procedures Manual | Due Date :11-Jan-2012

Finance Agreement: Madagascar National Parks Project Agreement: Schedule, Section II, B(3) | Description: MNP shall establish anaudit committee; strengthen internal audit reporting arrangements; prepare a comprehensive annual internal audit plan; and submitquarterly audit reports | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement: Madagascar National Parks Project Agreement: Schedule, Section IV, Paragraph 1 | Description: MadagascarNational Parks shall use its own internally generated revenues to cover the depreciation costs of equipment and other investmentsfinanced by the project. | Due Date :11-Jan-2012
